 According to the burial committee co-ordinator, Wambugu Karinga, at least Sh800,000 was needed to bury the victims.Â 
 Mr Karinga on Sunday said the families had agreed to have a joint funeral service at Ngai Ndeithia Secondary School tomorrow.




